</span></p><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-fbKhWw cWXGnG pf-67_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-leSCGb jlzrdC pf-68_"><strong>Legal action </strong>- Breaches in legislation can lead to fines, legal proceedings, and, in extreme cases, closure of the service.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-leSCGb jlzrdC pf-70_"><strong>Regulatory action </strong>- Regulators can take enforcement actions, issue warning notices, or put services in special measures.


</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-leSCGb jlzrdC pf-72_"><strong>Reputational damage </strong>- With increased public scrutiny, organisations found lacking can face negative publicity, leading to loss of trust and clientele.


